# Project Rules

- This project is `reportingetlservice.web`, an Angular 21 application written in TypeScript.
- Build and evolve the project as a modern Angular frontend, keeping Angular conventions, TypeScript correctness, and maintainable UI architecture in mind.
- This project uses TDD and BDD with Gherkin: describe behavior first in Gherkin scenarios, then implement it with focused automated tests and production code.
- The authoritative `swarmforge/` directory is always the version-controlled folder at the project root, as a sibling of folders such as `features/`, `src/`, and `.worktrees/`; it is never `.swarmforge/` and never a nested folder inside `.worktrees/`.
- Keep swarm state project-local under `.swarmforge/`, worktrees under `.worktrees/`, and helper scripts under `.worktrees/swarmtools/`.
- Prefer straightforward Angular application structure over custom runtime infrastructure unless the feature clearly requires it.
- Maintain clear role boundaries, reliable startup behavior, and explicit agent handoff mechanisms.
